---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import ScrollReveal from "../components/ScrollReveal.tsx";
import { SITE } from "../config/site.mjs";
---

<Layout
  title={`About | ${SITE.title}`}
  description="Giveth House is the physical home of the Giveth Galaxy — a community-driven Web3 hub in Barcelona open to builders, contributors, and communities since 2017."
  canonicalURL={`${SITE.url}/about`}
>
  <Header />
  <main id="main-content" role="main">
    <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 md:py-20">
      <ScrollReveal client:idle>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Giveth House</h1>
      </ScrollReveal>
      <ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.1}>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-12">
          A home for Web3 builders and communities — a living space for
          collaboration, experimentation, and connection in the heart of
          Barcelona.
        </p>
      </ScrollReveal>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

        <ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.2}>
          <h2>Story</h2>
          <p>
            Giveth was founded in 2016 by altruists who emerged from the early Ethereum
            ecosystem with a clear mission: build open, decentralized infrastructure to fund
            public goods and reward those who give to society and the world. A year later,
            Giveth House opened its doors in Barcelona — a physical anchor for a global,
            borderless community.
          </p>
          <p>
            The house was the vision of <strong>Griff Green</strong>, one of Giveth's founders
            and a central figure in the blockchain4good ecosystem. His idea was simple: in a
            world where most Web3 collaboration happens online, people still need real spaces
            to meet, share a table, and build the kind of trust that only comes from being in
            the same room. Since then, the house has quietly served as a meeting point for
            contributors across the decentralized ecosystem — people arrive for conferences,
            collaborations, or a few weeks of focused work, and often leave with new
            friendships, new projects, and a deeper connection to the community.
          </p>
        </ScrollReveal>

        <ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.3}>
          <h2>Why Barcelona</h2>
          <p>
            The choice of Barcelona was deliberate. Inspired by firsthand experience of the
            Catalan struggle for independence, Giveth's founders wanted to establish a haven
            that represents freedom of thought and freedom of choice — a physical space to
            exercise those freedoms in practice.
          </p>
          <p>
            Giveth House is open to and inclusive of all walks of life that carry equality,
            safety, camaraderie, and freedom from hierarchy in their philosophy. The Sants
            neighbourhood — historically rooted in workers' movements and cooperative
            culture — felt like a natural home for a solarpunk, blockchain4good community.
          </p>
        </ScrollReveal>

        <ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.4}>
          <h2>Community</h2>
          <p>
            Giveth House is the physical home of the Giveth Galaxy — an expanding community
            of interconnected projects and DAOs bound by a shared sense of common good.
            Over the years, the house has welcomed people connected to projects like
            Ethereum Foundation, Arbitrum, Starknet, Dappnode, Fuel Labs, dOrg, Vocdoni,
            Talent Layer, General Magic, and many others. Some stay for a few days, others
            for weeks — the common thread is a shared curiosity about building new systems
            for coordination, cooperation, and collective impact.
          </p>
          <p>
            More than just accommodation, the house acts as a{" "}
            <strong>Schelling point for the Web3 ecosystem</strong> — a place where
            collaborations, friendships, and new ideas emerge naturally.
          </p>
        </ScrollReveal>

        <ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.5}>
          <h2>Values</h2>
          <p>
            Giveth House is not a polished coworking space or a startup office, but a
            deliberately human place shaped by:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>openness and freedom of thought</li>
            <li>cooperation and camaraderie</li>
            <li>regenerative economics and public goods</li>
            <li>solarpunk optimism — building better systems together</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Many people describe the house as <strong>solarpunk</strong> — optimistic,
            collaborative, and oriented toward building better systems together. It is a
            place where the values behind the code become real.
          </p>
        </ScrollReveal>

        <ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.6}>
          <h2>Stewardship</h2>
          <p>
            Since 2022, the house has been stewarded by{" "}
            <strong>Franco Ruiz</strong>, who coordinates guest stays, maintains the space,
            organizes activities, and supports collaborations between residents and visitors.
          </p>
          <p>
            The house has grown over the years — most recently expanding to a third floor
            with a rooftop terrace, a long-dreamed-of open space for the community to breathe,
            gather, and enjoy Barcelona. In 2024, the neighbourhood demolition that had
            threatened the house was officially cancelled. Giveth House is here to stay.
          </p>
        </ScrollReveal>

        <ScrollReveal client:load delay={0.7}>
          <h2>Support the House</h2>
          <p>
            Giveth House exists because the community chooses to support it. Donations from
            contributors across the ecosystem help cover the practical realities of maintaining
            a shared space — rent, utilities, maintenance, and operations.
          </p>
          <p>
            The long-term vision is for the house to remain a free, open resource for the
            Web3 ecosystem — a physical place where the Giveth Galaxy lands on earth, and
            where the next generation of builders finds community, collaboration, and a warm
            place to land in Barcelona. Every contribution helps keep this small but
            meaningful corner of the blockchain4good world alive.
          </p>
        </ScrollReveal>

      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
